= â†’ Assignment Operator
Used to assign a value to a variable.

javascript
Copy
Edit
let x = 10; // Assigns value 10 to variable x
ğŸ”¹ == â†’ Loose Equality (Abstract Equality)
Compares values only, ignores data types.

If the types are different, JavaScript will coerce (convert) them before comparison.

javascript
Copy
Edit
console.log(5 == '5'); // âœ… true (string '5' is converted to number 5)
console.log(null == undefined); // âœ… true (both considered loosely equal)
ğŸ”¹ === â†’ Strict Equality
Compares both value and data type.

No type coercion is done.

javascript
Copy
Edit
console.log(5 === '5'); // âŒ false (number !== string)
console.log(5 === 5); // âœ… true
console.log(null === undefined); // âŒ false (different types)
